title: FDA moves to ease rules for blood donations from gay men
description: As a result of the FDA's new proposal, gay and bisexual men in monogamous relationships could soon be able to donate blood for the first time in decades.
author: By MATTHEW PERRONE - AP Health Writer

title: A high school basketball coach is still out $10,000 after Southwest canceled a flight and left his whole team stranded in Las Vegas for 5 days over Christmas. They ended up chartering a bus to drive 18 hours home in the snow.
